cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with video segmentation and recognition using a visual representation and a structured temporal model. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The use of generative models also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The experiments involve video datasets, indicating the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of statistical properties, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
